YOU NEED TO CONSULT THE PROBLEMS THAT EXIST HERE, you should come and take a tour to consult before deciding whether to let your relatives give birth here or not. 1. ATMOSPHERE: The delivery room is located next to the parking lot. Most of the ground floor area is used for parking purposes. In the same motorbike parking area is a system of rooms for normal births and cesarean sections. The atmosphere here is very unpleasant because the dust and smoke from the street seeps in through the parking lot where there are always cars going in and out. While the door into the delivery room is also the door out of the delivery room and the atmosphere here is very bad. If a healthy adult feels very uncomfortable while waiting, what can you say about the air quality inside the delivery room? 2. SANITATION: Currently the hospital is overloaded. Although the cleaning staff have made great efforts, the number is still very small compared to the number of people giving birth. It is necessary to strengthen the cleaning staff to be proportionate and appropriate. 3. SMELL: The bathroom structure is located in the nursing room, but the bathroom exhaust fan has been disabled, making the whole room very smelly. If this exhaust fan operates, the amount of outside air coming in will be the stinging air from the parking lot on the ground floor that rushes into the rooms on the upper floors due to the skylight design connecting directly from the parking area. As long as the ground floor is still used to park cars, this problem will still exist even if there is a restriction on starting the car engine when entering and exiting the parking area. Or solve it by opening the outside ventilation windows for each room and taking care of the bathroom exhaust system more often. Need to pay more attention to hygiene in the nursing room. 4. POST-BIRTH CARE: Cleaning for women after giving birth every day is very necessary, but most women do not dare to use this service a second time because it is very painful. Most family members help women clean every day even though they still have to pay for this service. 5. NOISE: The issue of visitation is not strictly enforced, allowing many relatives to bring children to stay with them, it is like a kindergarten for all ages so it is extremely noisy. Very sorry for the babies and mothers. If the hospital is comfortable with visits, it is necessary to arrange a place to rest for visitors. Currently, there are a lot of family members going to feed the children, making terrible noise with the children, carpets lying on the floor all over the place, not to mention food and garbage. This issue needs regular attention and monitoring. In particular, the problem of sound pollution is extremely serious. 6. COST: The advance for a normal birth here is currently 11 million VND, the price is not commensurate with the quality of service. Just like other places that emerged for a while and then became overloaded, here the quality of all postpartum services is deteriorating. The number of people coming to give birth is almost always overloaded. - I am someone who has used the services here and visited many other births, so I want to give my opinion to those who will be customers of the hospital as well as to the hospital's leadership. We hope that the hospital will try to improve more so that the next generation of people can use good services.

text: The hospital is very clean and professional but still needs improvement. It must be said that the hospital is clean and professional from every step because it corresponds to the amount of money the patient spends. There is quite a lot of green space in the hospital, making patients feel somewhat comfortable. Prices are of course higher than public hospitals. Health insurance is applied but pays very little, most patients pay themselves. The lowest price for a room to stay if accompanied by a caregiver is about 450k (after deducting health insurance). The staff also gives quite thoughtful instructions. I had an ENT check-up and my teeth were still quite OK. The doctor listens and explains to the patient. Anyone who wants a quick examination can make an appointment through the hotline to have an examination schedule and arrange flexible hours. If examined in the afternoon, it is more comfortable, less sick and does not need to be booked in advance. The canteen is also quite full of food and drinks, spacious and airy. Prices are a bit higher than outside. The second time I return to the hospital as a caregiver, I have a few comments: - Security is very good, full information is checked, the security guards are very welcoming when assisting. - Hygiene in the hospital is very good, but sometimes there is still a fishy smell in the ward hallway. If it could be improved, it would be great. - Regarding food, there is no food at the ward for patients like some other hospitals. It's a bit inconvenient because without family members, it is difficult for patients to buy food in the cafeteria. Food often runs out early in the lunch cafeteria. When I bought spring rolls in the morning, the dipping sauce was sour. If the patient couldn't distinguish the taste, if he ate it, he would get sick. Will the hospital be responsible? - The hospital is a public place, I agree, but the hospital should advise patients and family members about the rules and maintain general quiet. It is impossible to listen to chanting at 3:30 a.m. and listen to political news at 4:30 a.m. , other times the person making the video call loudly, filming all over the room. Columbia Asia Binh Duong Hospital is located in Thuan Giao - Thuan An, Binh Duong province, adjacent to Ho Chi Minh City. It is the first 100% foreign-invested international general hospital in Binh Duong province. Columbia Asia Binh Duong was put into operation in 2012 with a scale of 100 beds to serve the daily needs of patients from health care services with a full range of specialties, surgery, paraclinical, diagnostic imaging and customer care services. We provide medical services with the motto of early diagnosis, early intervention and treatment from common diseases to complex cases. Our patients are cared for according to each individual's individual needs. For that reason, Columbia Asia Binh Duong is always the top choice of foreign experts working in Vietnam in particular and the Binh Duong community in general. We are pleased to serve you whenever you need us. We will continue to strive to improve services to bring the utmost comfort and satisfaction to our patients.

text: I will tell everyone my true story when I came here for examination. Real people, real things. Before coming here for check-up, I googled and read the reviews of this hospital, most of them criticized the reception and reception process. After reading it, I was quite disappointed. However, when I went to the doctor's office and mentally prepared myself from the moment I entered the medical registration counter, things were very different. Probably because I'm unlucky. The hospital is not crowded, there is no jostling, it is very orderly and quiet. The receptionist at counter number 2 welcomed me very gently and thoughtfully. She gave me very gentle instructions and communication. Because it was my first visit, I needed to put more information on a handwritten note. She guided me very carefully. Lovely, not curt or angry... Next, someone pressed the elevator and took me to the 3rd floor to have my blood pressure measured and wait for the doctor. Very quick, no waiting even though it was Monday morning at the beginning of the week. Until I got in to see the doctor, he was a dermatologist. First of all, the facilities here are very good, clean, luxurious and what I like most is the privacy. I can comfortably tell everything to the doctor without fear of other people hearing it. This is what I like the most and look forward to the most when going to the doctor. Then the doctor examined me and advised me very carefully, without being angry, scolding or curt. And special . The doctor did not diagnose the disease or give me any tests at my request even though I requested it. He also refused to sell me medicine because he said I had no disease at all. Although I really want to buy a bag of medicine to bring home for peace of mind.... Thanks to that, I was able to relieve my fear before going to the doctor. That day, I paid 315k for the examination and left feeling very happy and feeling like it was worth the money I spent.... Please send a compliment to the receptionist at counter number 2 and thank you to Dr. Thuy An, dermatology department

text: The hospital quality is good, clean and airy. I've been to the doctor many times, but today is very strange. Today I had a follow-up check-up and everything was good until I got to the cashier counter (counter number 3). The cashier called my name to the counter and said it was three million six hundred (I couldn't hear right behind me). I said again that the payment was too much, I didn't bring enough for me to go out and buy medicine, I just paid. Only pay for medical examination costs and any medications that health insurance will pay for. The attitude immediately changed, asking why didn't you say it from the beginning, I said no one asked where you were but you said it. She asked health insurance to pay for thirty thousand, I can ask for as much as possible. Then tell me to tell the doctor this and that and then ask me to wait. Ok, I waited another 40 minutes. During that 40 minutes of waiting, a call came from the hospital asking me why I didn't get the medicine and I also said the reason (I'm not comfortable saying it here) and I also said I was still treated according to the regimen. from the doctor, then counter 3 called my name to the counter and said that after deducting the medicine, I still had to pay: three million, one hundred, tens of thousands more. I was startled and asked her twice: Ms. Check again for me, before I quit smoking it was more than three million six hundred but now I quit smoking it's more than three million one?? I bought that prescription for more than 2 million. She asked if you wanted to print it so I printed it out for you to check, then she printed it out and I saw it and still saw it was more than three million one and I said no problem, I agreed to pay and she pulled out the bill. The paper just printed out in a flash. Then she looked back on the screen and said: Oh, yours is just over a million and two left. I told you right away, I told you to double check for me, but you were sure it was more than three million one, but now you say it's more than one million two, what do you mean? She snapped: So can I apologize? Let's say OK. After that, she still guided me to get medicine and wait for the nurse at counter A to give me the medical certificate. But such a condescending attitude towards customers is unacceptable. We are patients but we are customers so we also need to have certain respect. I hope I won't see you again next time. February 20, 2023.

The examination schedule will have to be according to the doctor's schedule, so sometimes conflicts with personal schedules will be accepted. Registering documents is quite quick, but there is also a problem with data synchronization when staff forget to update medical records into the system, leading to records not matching when admitted to the hospital, and having to communicate in circles. Evaluating the examination service for nearly 9 months as good, ignoring minor incidents due to human problems that are difficult to avoid. The quality of the birth package service is good, just bring clothes and personal items, the hospital takes care of all the prenatal examinations, delivery, postpartum... as long as you pay enough money. The nurses' offices are on duty 24/7, providing enthusiastic support when requested, but the stalls and teen rooms are open during business hours, so if you need to buy anything late at night, you can buy it yourself outside. As a general hospital with spacious and superior infrastructure in the Ben Cat area with investment from owner Becamex, My Phuoc General Hospital has an important position because it is located in an area adjacent to many industrial parks. The major industry of Ben Cat Town, where people and hundreds of thousands of workers live and work, need to be examined and treated every day further than the areas of Bau Bang, Chon Thanh, Binh Long, Binh Long. Phuoc also focuses on medical examination and treatment here due to the closer distance to Saigon, in addition to the treatment of a number of experienced older doctors who have worked at large hospitals in Saigon for many years. Patients praise it, but unfortunately, with a young team of doctors and nurses, the process of medical examination and treatment is still limited, and the medical equipment and machinery are not up to par so the treatment can really be done. The accuracy is not yet complete, so more or less patients and family members who visit the patient directly complain, and since the inauguration of the new infrastructure, we have noticed that fewer and fewer people come for medical examination and treatment. Private hospitals near newly opened industrial parks such as: Nhan Nghia clinic (My Phuoc 2), Hoang Hao (My Phuoc 3) further away is Van Phuc (VSIP 2), however if daily limitations are not overcome My Phuoc hospital's leading position will no longer exist, which is a pity.
